cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper is about improving the performance of information retrieval models using neural networks and pseudo-relevance feedback. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes an end-to-end neural framework, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experiments on standard test collections, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
